{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"young-capitate-lorikeet","description":"## Why\nThe design has sharp edges (hot-path cost, concurrency on the shared branch, rate-limit, no_mutate,\nabsent marker). Only tests lock the invariants so future ensures can be added safely.\n\n## What\nAdd tests covering: git-level idempotency (`run_ensures` twice on a converged store → zero new\ncommits); hot-path regression (a write never invokes `run_ensures`, no git-config subprocess,\n≤1 applied-set read/process); staleness-hint (stale store hints once, rate-limited to 24h,\nsuppressible, fresh-init worktree silent); concurrency (two processes sweeping the same checkout\nconverge; markers written atomically, no torn state); no_mutate (read-only fsck mutates nothing);\nabsent/garbage marker (→ empty set → converges, no re-commit storm).\n\n## Scope\nIn: the test suite for WS1-3 invariants. Out: the feature code itself (WS1-3), docs (WS4).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Idempotency test: `run_ensures()` twice on a converged store makes zero new commits/pushes\n- [ ] Hot-path regression test: a ticket mutation never calls `run_ensures`, spawns no git-config subprocess, and reads the applied-set at most once per process\n- [ ] Staleness-hint tests: stale store hints once; rate-limited to ≤1/24h; env var suppresses; fresh auto-init'd worktree stays silent\n- [ ] Concurrency test: two processes sweeping the same checkout converge with atomic, non-torn markers\n- [ ] no_mutate + absent-marker tests: read-only fsck mutates nothing; missing/garbage marker degrades to empty-set without crashing","id":"f9b6-744e-636b-4430","parent_id":"9ccb-27ee-24dd-4944","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"WS5: tests — idempotency, hot-path regression, staleness-hint, concurrency, no_mutate, absent-marker"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783569046378227001,"uuid":"db2616bc-0ea9-4594-8ccf-f407c6c77cf0"}